msgid "Spelling"
msgstr "Črkovanje"

#. Tag: keyword
#: index.docbook:25
#, no-c-format
msgid "dictionary"
msgstr "slovar"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The configuration options available here are used as default by all &kde; "
"applications that use &sonnet;, which is a frontend to various free spell "
"checkers."
msgstr ""
"Nastavitvene možnosti, ki so na voljo tukaj, privzeto uporabljajo vse "
"aplikacije &kde;, ki uporabljajo &sonnet;, ki je vmesnik za različne "
"brezplačne programe za preverjanje črkovanja."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:35
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To use &sonnet; you need to install spell checkers like &eg; <ulink url="
"\"http://aspell.net/\">&GNU; Aspell</ulink>, <ulink url=\"http://hspell."
"ivrix.org.il/\">Hspell</ulink> or <ulink url=\"https://hunspell.github.io/"
"\">Hunspell</ulink> and additionally the corresponding dictionaries for your "
"language."
msgstr ""
"Za uporabo &sonnet; morate namestiti programe za preverjanje črkovanja, kot "
"so &eg; <ulink url=\"http://aspell.net/\">&GNU; Aspell</ulink>, <ulink url="
"\"http://hspell.ivrix.org.il/\">Hspell</ulink> ali <ulink url=\"https://"
"hunspell.github.io/\">Hunspell</ulink> poleg ustreznih slovarjev za vaš "
"jezik."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:41
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The configuration options selected here can be overridden by each "
"application."
msgstr ""
"Možnosti konfiguracije, ki so izbrane tukaj, lahko vsaka aplikacija prekliče."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the drop down box <guilabel>Default language</guilabel> choose from the "
"available dictionaries, which one to use for &sonnet;."
msgstr ""
"V spustnem oknu <guilabel>Privzet jezik</guilabel> med razpoložljivimi "
"slovarji izberite, katerega želite uporabiti za &sonnet;."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Options"
msgstr "Možnosti"

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid "Enable autodetection of language"
msgstr "Omogoči samodejno zaznavanje jezika"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This feature is based on several heuristics (script used, trigram matching "
"and language ranking on available languages in the spell-checking backend). "
"This allows it to automatically switch language in a multi-language document."
msgstr ""
"Ta funkcija temelji na več hevrističnih metodah (uporabljena pisava, "
"ujemanje trigramov in razvrstitev jezikov na podlagi razpoložljivih jezikov "
"v zaledju preverjanja črkovanja). Tako lahko samodejno preklopi jezik v "
"večjezičnem dokumentu."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:62
#, no-c-format
msgid "Automatic spell checking enabled by default"
msgstr "Samodejno preverjanje črkovanja je privzeto omogočeno"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:64
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a mark is placed in this checkbox, the spelling of words will be check in "
"your document as you type them. Misspelled will have a red line drawn under "
"them."
msgstr ""
"Če označite to potrditveno polje, se v dokumentu preveri črkovanje besed, ko "
"jih vnesete. Pod napačno zapisanimi besedami bo narisana rdeča črta."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip all uppercase words"
msgstr "Preskoči vse besede z velikimi črkami"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If a mark is placed in this checkbox, the spelling of any word which "
"consists of all capital letters will not be checked."
msgstr ""
"Če označite to potrditveno polje, se ne preveri črkovanje katere koli "
"besede, ki je sestavljena iz vseh velikih črk."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:75
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is useful for document using a large number of acronyms. If this box is "
"left unchecked, most of those acronyms will be incorrectly marked. By "
"placing a mark in this checkbox, the acronyms will not be marked as "
"misspelled."
msgstr ""
"To je uporabno za dokumente, ki vsebujejo veliko število kratic. Če tega "
"polja ne označite, bo večina teh kratic nepravilno označena. Če označite to "
"polje, akronimi ne bodo označeni kot napačno napisani."

#. Tag: guilabel
#: index.docbook:82
#, no-c-format
msgid "Skip run-together words"
msgstr "Preskočite skupne besede"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:83
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If this box is not checked, then words that appear in the dictionary "
"separately, but have been run together, are considered to be spelling "
"errors. Examples of such words are shutout, cannot, and blackout."
msgstr ""
"Če to polje ni označeno, se besede, ki so v slovarju prikazane ločeno, "
"vendar so bile združene, obravnavajo kot pravopisne napake. Takšne besede so "
"na primer polnoč, vinograd, morebiti."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Checking this box will help prevent applications from flagging website and "
"email addresses for spelling errors. These addresses often contain words run "
"together."
msgstr ""
"Če potrdite to polje, boste preprečili, da bi aplikacije označile spletne "
"strani in e-poštne naslove zaradi pravopisnih napak. Ti naslovi pogosto "
"vsebujejo besede, ki so sestavljene skupaj."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:96
#, no-c-format
msgid "Ignored words"
msgstr "Prezrte besede"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:97
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The bottom half of the dialog box allows you to designate specific words "
"(they may be specialized terminology, proper names, &etc;) which should be "
"ignored by the spelling program."
msgstr ""
"V spodnjem delu pogovornega okna lahko določite določene besede (lahko gre "
"za specializirano terminologijo, lastna imena &etc;), ki jih program za "
"črkovanje ne bo upošteval."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:100
#, no-c-format
msgid "Adding a word to the ignore list"
msgstr "Dodajanje besede na seznam prezrtih besed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To add a word, type the word in the text box and click the <guibutton>Add</"
"guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite dodati besedo, jo vnesite v besedilno polje in kliknite gumb "
"<guibutton>Dodaj</guibutton>."

#. Tag: title
#: index.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid "Deleting a word from the ignore list"
msgstr "Brisanje besede s seznama prezrtih besed"

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:105
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"To remove a word, select the word in the listbox containing all the "
"currently ignored words by clicking on it with the &LMB;. Now click the "
"<guibutton>Remove</guibutton> button."
msgstr ""
"Če želite odstraniti besedo, jo izberite v seznamu, ki vsebuje vse trenutno "
"prezrte besede, tako da kliknete nanjo z &LMB;. Zdaj kliknite gumb "
"<guibutton>Odstrani</guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When you are happy with the changes, simply click <guibutton>Apply</"
"guibutton>."
msgstr ""
"Ko ste s spremembami zadovoljni, preprosto kliknite <guibutton>Potrdi</"
"guibutton>."

#. Tag: para
#: index.docbook:111
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Clicking on the <guibutton>Defaults</guibutton> button restores all values "
"to their default values."
msgstr ""
"S klikom na gumb <guibutton>Privzete vrednosti</guibutton> povrnete vse "
"vrednosti na privzete vrednosti."

#~ msgid "Create root/affix combinations not in dictionary"
#~ msgstr "Ustvari kombinacije predpona/koren/pripona, ki niso v slovarju"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "Selecting this option allows the spell checker to register as "
#~ "<quote>correct</quote> combinations of root words with suffixes or "
#~ "prefixes even if the particular combination is not listed in its "
#~ "dictionary database of words."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Izbira te možnosti omogoča preverjalniku črkovanja, da registrira kot "
#~ "<quote>pravilne</quote> kombinacije korenskih besed s predponami ali "
#~ "priponami, tudi če določena kombinacija ni navedeno v slovarski zbirki "
#~ "besed."

#~ msgid "Consider run-together words as spelling errors"
#~ msgstr "Obravnavaj skupaj pisane besede kot napake"

#~ msgid "Dictionary:"
#~ msgstr "Slovar:"

#~ msgid "Encoding:"
#~ msgstr "Kodni nabor:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "You should select the one that matches the character set you are using. "
#~ "In some cases, dictionaries will support more than one encoding. A "
#~ "dictionary might, for example, accept accented characters when "
#~ "<emphasis>Latin1</emphasis> is selected, but accept email-style character "
#~ "combinations (like <userinput>'a</userinput> for an accented <emphasis>a</"
#~ "emphasis>) when <emphasis>7-Bit-ASCII</emphasis> is selected. Please see "
#~ "your dictionary's distribution for more information."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Izbrati bi morali tistega, ki ustreza uporabljanemu naboru. V nekaterih "
#~ "primerih bodo slovarji podpirali več kot en kodni nabor. Slovar bo morda "
#~ "sprejel naglašene znake pri izbranemu naboru <emphasis>Latin1</emphasis>, "
#~ "vendar pa jih bo sprejel kot kombinacije črk iz e-pošte (npr. "
#~ "<userinput>'a</userinput> za naglašen <emphasis>á</emphasis>), ko je "
#~ "izbran <emphasis>7-bitni ASCII</emphasis>. Za več informacij poglejte v "
#~ "distribucijo vašega slovarja."

#~ msgid "Client:"
#~ msgstr "Odjemnik:"

#~ msgid ""
#~ "You can choose which of the installed client applications on your system "
#~ "to use. For example, you can choose <command>ispell</command>."
#~ msgstr ""
#~ "Izberete lahko, kateri izmed nameščenih odjemalskih programov se naj "
#~ "uporabi. Npr., izberete lahko <command>ispell</command>."
